## ALL RES METHODS

Method ->	Purpose

res.send()	Sends a response of various types (string, object, buffer, etc.) and ends the response.
res.json()	Sends a JSON response (sets Content-Type: application/json).
res.status()	Sets the HTTP status code for the response.
res.sendStatus()	Sets the status code and sends its string representation as the response body.
res.end()	Ends the response process without sending any data.
res.sendFile()	Sends a file as an HTTP response.
res.download()	Prompts a file download by setting appropriate headers.
res.render()	Renders a view template and sends the rendered HTML to the client.
res.redirect()	Redirects the client to a specified URL with an optional status code.
res.set() / res.header()	Sets HTTP headers for the response.
res.get()	Gets the value of a specified response header.
res.append()	Appends a value to a specified HTTP response header.
res.cookie()	Sets a cookie in the response.
res.clearCookie()	Clears a cookie in the response.
res.jsonp()	Sends a JSON response with JSONP support.
res.links()	Sets the Link HTTP header with provided links.
res.location()	Sets the Location HTTP header for redirects.
res.attachment()	Sets the response to indicate a file attachment (download).
res.locals	An object to pass data to the view templates.

